 f(x) = \begin{cases} x &y\lt x\le1 \\ a-x&1\lt x\le2\\ 0&\mbox{else} \end{cases}
a
\int_{0}^{1}xdx+\int_{1}^{2}(a-x)dx=1.
\left[\frac{1}{2}x^2\right]_0^1+\left[ax-\frac 12x^2\right]_1^2=1
\Rightarrow \left(\frac{1}{2}1^2-\frac 120^2\right)+\left(a\cdot 2-\frac 12\cdot2^2\right)-\left(a\cdot 1-\frac 12\cdot 1^2\right)=1
\Rightarrow \frac 12+(2a-2)-\left(a-\frac 12\right)=1\Rightarrow a=2.
P(0.5\lt X\lt 1.5)=\int_{0.5}^{1}xdx+\int_{1}^{1.5}(2-x)dx.
E(X)=m=\int_{0}^{1}x\cdot xdx+\int_{1}^{2}x\cdot(2-x)dx,
V(X)=\int_{0}^{1}(x-m)^2\cdot xdx+\int_{1}^{2}(x-m)^2(2-x)dx.
